cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL. 

The paper discusses the evaluation of algorithms for automatically extracting keywords and keyphrases from documents, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The use of machine learning algorithms (such as Eric Brill's part-of-speech tagger) and the comparison of different algorithms also suggest that cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.DL are possible sub-categories.
